{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01Qt8f1q1F4nWBtUQWsfoq4g","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ **PASS** — the proof is complete and verified with no cheating detected.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe theorem `VInv3 => VInv1` is logically trivial since `VInv1` (vote-uniqueness for a *single* acceptor) is just the special case of `VInv3` (vote-uniqueness *across all* acceptors) where `a1 = a2`. But `PROOF OBVIOUS` failed because TLAPS doesn't expand the `VInv1`/`VInv3` definitions or perform the needed quantifier instantiation on its own.\n\nThe fix replaces `PROOF OBVIOUS` with a two-step structured proof:\n\n```tla\nTHEOREM VInv3 => VInv1\n<1> SUFFICES ASSUME VInv3,\n                    NEW a \\in Acceptor, NEW b \\in Ballot,\n                    NEW v \\in Value, NEW w \\in Value,\n                    VotedFor(a, b, v), VotedFor(a, b, w)\n             PROVE  v = w\n  BY DEF VInv1\n<1> QED\n  BY DEF VInv3\n```\n\n- The **`SUFFICES`** step unfolds `VInv1` (`BY DEF VInv1`), stripping its universal quantifiers and implication so the goal becomes \"given the two votes, show `v = w`.\"\n- The **`QED`** step unfolds `VInv3` (`BY DEF VInv3`); the backend instantiates `a1 := a, a2 := a` and discharges the goal from the two `VotedFor` hypotheses.\n\nBoth obligations are proved, and `./check_proof_bin VoteProof_VInv1.tla --level 2` reports PASS. No existing declarations, definitions, or the theorem statement were modified — only the placeholder proof was replaced."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":516,"cache_read_input_tokens":20021,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":516},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5472e5c8-8cce-4b25-869e-83fc35245f7c","uuid":"cf51ad00-a6b9-